{
  "texts": [
    "Document co-citation clustering analysis (DCCA)In this section, we discuss a Document Co-Citation Clustering Analysis (DCCA) of the research field, where documents are grouped by their citation links.",
    "DCCA is a method for finding out the clusters of the documents which are cited together by using in CiteSpace.",
    "This is helpful for researchers to establish new trends in a particular field, monitor the development of topics of interest, and showcase significant publications in a specific subject area.",
    "For readers, DCCA helps save time by making literature reviews more efficient, uncovering relationships between different fields of research, and highlighting gaps in the literature, thus providing a better understanding of the knowledge map [70].",
    "Table 3 summarises the most cited academic works in the area of DFIG-based WECS."
  ]
}